webResources.textAttributionSnippet: (en) Motif from Grebo 1943. The church of the resort, which, at the time of its design, created waves of emotion in the village. When Christer Lindblom took up the post in Grebo in 1745, he immediately considered that the new parish church was in need. Since the church in the parish Värna was in poor condition, he expressed the idea that a new church could serve both parishes in common. After more than twenty years of reasoning, the church had been renovated in the Värna, which is why new ones were not up to date. In Grebo’s husband about the church being erected in the place it is now located, drink 100 meters northeast of the old. On May 11, 1772, the construction work began and on the 16th Sunday after three-fold, which that year came into being on October 4, the first service was celebrated - https://www.europeana.eu/item/73/S_OM_photo_OMFB000631. AB Flygtrafik. Östergötlands museum - http://digitaltmuseum.se/021016419921. Public Domain Mark - http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/mark/1.0/
